│ 454   //      that we can compare pointers                                    │
│ 455   //    - We wouldn't be able to merge two pointers for which we need     │
│ 456   //      to emit a memcheck. The classes in DepCands are already         │
│ 457   //      conveniently built such that no two pointers in the same        │
│ 458   //      class need checking against each other.                         │
│ 459                                                                           │
│ 460   // We use the following (greedy) algorithm to construct the groups      │
│ 461   // For every pointer in the equivalence class:                          │
│ 462   //   For each existing group:                                           │
│ 463   //   - if the difference between this pointer and the min/max bounds    │
│ 464   //     of the group is a constant, then make the pointer part of the    │
